{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, Elastic Security supports distributed deployment and new nodes can be added to the cluster to achieve scalability.",
    "The community edition of SIEMonster supports only a single server with up to 100 endpoints, while the multi-server and multi-tenant options are only available in paid versions.",
    "OSSIM is also limited in terms of scalability and does not support multi-tier distributed deployment.",
    "Wazuh has the capability to detect vulnerabilities in the installed applications.",
    "Wazuh achieves this by building a global vulnerability database from Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE) repositories and generating alerts when a CVE affects a package installed on the monitored devices."
  ]
}